WEBVTT

00:02.306 --> 00:03.786
-PREVIOUSLY ON "OUTSIDERS"...

00:03.916 --> 00:06.658
-WITH THIS OAK,
OUR NEW LEADER TAKES RULE.

00:06.789 --> 00:10.010
BUT IF THE OAK BE TAKEN
IN A MANNER IMPURE,

00:10.140 --> 00:12.490
SO THE NEW BREN'IN
SHALL NOT ENDURE.

00:12.621 --> 00:14.014
SHOULDN'T BE NO CONCERN TO YOU.

00:14.144 --> 00:15.972
-WELL, I GOT NO CONCERN.

00:16.103 --> 00:17.756
-IT DON'T MAKE SENSE.

00:17.887 --> 00:20.237
SHE TOOK A BATH.
THE WATER WAS STILL IN THE TUB.

00:20.368 --> 00:22.022
BUT HER TOWEL WAS SITTIN'
WHERE I LEFT IT,

00:22.152 --> 00:23.588
IT WAS FOLDED UP,
AND IT WEREN'T DAMP.

00:23.719 --> 00:25.982
-IF SHE DIDN'T GO,
WE'D ALL BE GONE.

00:26.113 --> 00:27.375
-G'WIN KNOWS.

00:27.505 --> 00:30.943
-WILL YOU BE MY QUEEN,
G'WINVEER?

00:31.074 --> 00:32.380
-I ACCEPT.

00:32.510 --> 00:34.295
-WE'VE RUN INTO
SOME BUMPS IN THE ROAD.

00:34.425 --> 00:36.514
BY THAT, I MEAN THE FARRELLS.
-WE KNOW WHERE THEY LIVE.

00:36.645 --> 00:38.777
RIGHT UP THERE ON THAT MOUNTAIN,
KEEPING US FROM JOBS.

00:38.908 --> 00:41.476
-TAKE 'EM OUT TO A BAR.
BUY 'EM SOME DRINKS.

00:41.606 --> 00:43.130
-WE GOTTA GET THEM DOWN
OFF OF THERE.

00:43.260 --> 00:44.957
-HELL, ONE OF THEM TRIED
TO SCREW MY SISTER.

00:45.088 --> 00:50.267
-ONLY IDEA I GOT
IS TO GO UP THERE AND KILL 'EM.

00:50.398 --> 00:52.704
-[ PANTING ]
[ GUN COCKS ]

00:52.835 --> 00:56.534
-I GOT SOMETHIN' FOR THAT BACK,
AND SOME TEQUILA.

00:56.665 --> 00:58.667
♪♪

00:58.797 --> 00:59.929
[ THUD ]

01:00.060 --> 01:02.888
[ GLASS SHATTERS, THUD ]

01:03.019 --> 01:05.543
-YOU GET SOME HELP, OR I'M
TAKING THAT BOY AWAY FROM YOU.

01:05.674 --> 01:07.110
-HEY, IS CALEB HERE?

01:07.241 --> 01:08.503
-WAIT, WAIT.
WHEN DID THEY LAST SEE HIM?

01:08.633 --> 01:10.548
-I-I DON'T KNOW.
-LEDDA, WHERE IS HE?!

01:10.679 --> 01:12.550
CALEB!

01:12.681 --> 01:14.074
[ RUSTLING AND RUMBLING ]

01:16.467 --> 01:18.034
-THIS ABOUT THE FUTURE
OF THE CLAN.

01:18.165 --> 01:21.820
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY TO DEAL
WITH SOME PEOPLE -- FIRE.

01:21.951 --> 01:24.084
-SAYS YOU GOT
A JUG OF YOUR WINE TO TRADE.

01:24.214 --> 01:28.262
THIS BABY WILL MAKE
AN IMPRESSION.

01:28.392 --> 01:31.830
[ COCKS GUN, MACHINE GUNFIRE ]

01:34.311 --> 01:36.792
-I CAN GET YOU A HUNDRED MORE
WHERE THOSE CAME FROM.

01:38.402 --> 01:42.102
♪♪

01:42.232 --> 01:46.280
-♪ THE DAWN IS UP, THERE'S
FIRE ON THE MOUNTAIN ♪

01:46.410 --> 01:50.327
♪ THEY'LL HAVE TO ANSWER
FOR THEIR CROOKED PLAN ♪

01:50.458 --> 01:53.417
♪ THE HOLLOWS
WILL SURROUND THEM ♪

01:53.548 --> 01:55.332
♪ AND THEY'LL GO RUNNIN'

01:55.463 --> 01:59.162
♪ BACK TO THE WRETCHED REALM
THEY CAME ♪

02:01.382 --> 02:07.823
♪ NOR WILL THE DOGS OF HELL
REFRAIN ♪

02:07.953 --> 02:13.481
♪ AND THE LAND WILL SUFFER
THOSE WHO PAID ♪

02:18.442 --> 02:20.749
♪♪

02:20.879 --> 02:22.838
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]
-JUST THROW IT.

02:22.968 --> 02:24.144
YOU AIN'T GONNA WIN.
JUST THROW IT.

02:24.274 --> 02:26.624
AH! [ LAUGHS ]

02:26.755 --> 02:28.713
[ SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ]
-YOU AIN'T GOT IT.

02:28.844 --> 02:31.151
YOU AIN'T -- LET'S SEE.
YOU AIN'T GONNA GET IT.

02:31.281 --> 02:33.544
AH, HA HA!
-COME ON, GIVE ME A WIN.

02:33.675 --> 02:35.067
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]
-COME ON.

02:35.198 --> 02:37.244
-YOU AIN'T GOT NOTHIN'.
-OH! [ LAUGHS ] YES!

02:37.374 --> 02:39.681
-YOU NICKED!
-AIN'T NICKED!

02:39.811 --> 02:41.204
-SHUT YOURSELF.

02:41.335 --> 02:42.771
AIN'T MY FAULT
THEY TURNED AGAINST YA.

02:42.901 --> 02:44.251
-YOU'RE A CHEAT.

02:44.381 --> 02:46.557
-RATHER BE A CHEAT
THAN A WHINY LITTLE BITCH.

02:46.688 --> 02:48.559
-NOW YOU'RE TALKING
LAST NIGHT, HUH?

02:48.690 --> 02:50.170
-THOSE ARE MY WINNINGS,
NOT YOURS.

02:50.300 --> 02:55.523
TRY AND KEEP UP WITH ME...
-GUYS! OPEN YOUR EYES.

02:55.653 --> 02:58.656
-WHOA. I COME IN PEACE.

02:58.787 --> 03:00.571
-MAKE YOU ALL MY SENTRY WARDS.

03:00.702 --> 03:03.705
Y'ALL LET A CRAZY MAN IN HERE
LIKE HE'S A BUG.

03:07.056 --> 03:08.275
GET YOUR ASS INSIDE.

03:11.191 --> 03:15.760
THAT HAPPENS AGAIN...
YOU WON'T LIKE IT.

03:17.284 --> 03:20.200
[ SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ]
...MY SENTRY WARDS?

03:20.330 --> 03:22.941
GROW UP. DO IT NOW.

03:24.247 --> 03:26.945
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

03:27.076 --> 03:29.861
-YOU LIKE IT? [ SIGHS ]
-MM.

03:29.992 --> 03:33.561
WELL, IT AIN'T MUCH USE TO ME
WITHOUT AMMUNITION.

03:33.691 --> 03:35.519
BUT MAYBE THAT'S WHY
YOU BURNED IT ALL LAST NIGHT

03:35.650 --> 03:37.347
BEFORE GIVING IT TO ME.

03:37.478 --> 03:40.220
-I WAS JUST TRYING TO GET YOUR
UNDIVIDED ATTENTION, IS ALL.

03:40.350 --> 03:41.917
-WELL, COME TO THINK ON IT,

03:42.047 --> 03:44.441
THERE ARE
A COUPLE ROUNDS LEFT IN IT.

03:44.572 --> 03:46.530
MM?

03:48.793 --> 03:50.404
[ HAMMER CLICKS ]

03:50.534 --> 03:52.319
-GUESS NOT.

03:54.495 --> 03:57.889
-YOU SAID YOU COULD GET ME
A HUNDRED MORE LIKE THIS.

03:58.020 --> 03:59.674
-I CAN AND I WILL.

03:59.804 --> 04:01.719
SEE, THE FOLKS I'M DEALIN' WITH
DOWN THERE,

04:01.850 --> 04:03.765
THEY HAVE AN AFFECTION
FOR FARRELL WINE.

04:03.895 --> 04:08.204
MEANING YOU GRANT ME MORE WINE,
AND I CAN GET YOU MORE FIRE.

04:08.335 --> 04:10.206
-WE TAKE WHAT WE WANT FROM THEM.

04:10.337 --> 04:12.513
WE DON'T SULLY OURSELVES WITH
THEIR AFFAIRS OR THEIR MONEY.

04:12.643 --> 04:13.862
YOU KNOW THIS.

04:13.992 --> 04:15.994
-WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO,
CUT OFF MY HAND?

04:16.125 --> 04:17.561
-LET HIM DIRTY HIMSELF.

04:17.692 --> 04:19.084
YOU STAY UP HERE WITH US,
PROTECTED.

04:19.215 --> 04:23.306
-I THOUGHT THAT GUNS MADE US
WEAK, MY QUEEN.

04:23.437 --> 04:26.266
-YOU'RE THE BREN'IN.

04:26.396 --> 04:28.442
-WELL...WELL, THEN GO
DIRTY YOURSELF, BOY.

04:28.572 --> 04:31.445
YOU HEARD MY WOMAN.
-WHAT I HEARD WAS "QUEEN."

04:31.575 --> 04:33.403
QUEEN?
-OH, THAT'S RIGHT.

04:33.534 --> 04:36.841
HE WASN'T THERE. NO.

04:36.972 --> 04:39.366
WELL, I WAS NEVER
THE MARRYING KIND.

04:39.496 --> 04:42.804
BUT I GOT TO THINKIN'
THAT IT AIN'T RIGHT

04:42.934 --> 04:46.373
THAT THE THE BREN'IN NOT HAVE
A WIFE, SO...

04:46.503 --> 04:50.638
I OFFERED, AND SHE ACCEPTED.

04:53.815 --> 04:55.817
-LET'S GET BACK
TO OUR CONVERSATION.

04:55.947 --> 04:58.863
-YOU GET ME SAID FIRE
FOR THE COMING WAR,

04:58.994 --> 05:03.520
YOU'LL BE GOOD WITH ME
AND THIS MOUNTAIN FOR ALL TIME.

05:03.651 --> 05:06.349
-FINE. DONE AND DONE.

05:06.480 --> 05:09.309
I MEAN, YOU'RE OKAY WITH THAT?
YOU GOOD?

05:09.439 --> 05:13.313
-WELL, I SURE AM. HUH?
HOW ABOUT YOU?

05:13.443 --> 05:15.967
-OH, I'VE NEVER BEEN BETTER.

05:19.406 --> 05:21.277
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

05:21.408 --> 05:24.541
-YOUR TEA'S GONNA GET COLD.
-MM-HMM.

05:30.112 --> 05:31.896
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

05:32.027 --> 05:33.811
-[ LAUGHING ]
-WHO'S THE BIG MAN?

05:33.942 --> 05:36.031
WHO'S THE WILD MAN NOW, HUH?

05:36.161 --> 05:38.033
MR. WILD MAN WITH HIS FISTS!

05:38.163 --> 05:40.862
[ LAUGHTER ]
HUH?!

05:40.992 --> 05:43.908
HUH?! HUH?! HUH?!

05:44.039 --> 05:46.868
UHH! I SHOULD KILL YOU
FOR WHAT YOU DONE TO MY SISTER.

05:46.998 --> 05:48.304
-OHH! [ LAUGHS ]

05:48.435 --> 05:50.001
-HEY, HEY,
LET UP A SECOND, JAMES.

05:50.132 --> 05:51.438
I THINK THE BOY COULD USE
A DRINK.

05:51.568 --> 05:53.788
-HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!
DON'T WASTE THAT.

05:53.918 --> 05:56.138
-BREECE, WE GOT US A FARRELL!
LOOK!

05:56.268 --> 05:59.184
-[ GROANS ]
-[ LAUGHING ]

05:59.315 --> 06:01.926
-STOP IT.

06:02.057 --> 06:03.580
WHAT IN THE HELL
ARE Y'ALL THINKIN'?

06:03.711 --> 06:05.365
BUNCH OF DUMB SHITS!

06:05.495 --> 06:07.497
YOU GOT HIM NOW. WHAT YOU GUYS
PLANNING ON DOING WITH HIM?

06:07.628 --> 06:09.499
HE'S A PERSON, YOU KNOW?
YOU GONNA LET HIM GO,

06:09.630 --> 06:11.066
HE'S GONNA GO TO THE COPS!

06:11.196 --> 06:12.676
OR WORSE, HE RUNS BACK UP TOP,

06:12.807 --> 06:15.157
BRINGS DOWN A BUNCH OF CRAZIES
AND KILLS US ALL!

06:15.287 --> 06:18.595
-I LIKE TO THINK THAT
THEY WOULD.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.118
[ EXHALES ]

06:20.249 --> 06:24.340
-WHAT'D YOU SAY TO ME?
-NO! LEAVE HIM ALONE!

06:24.471 --> 06:26.777
AND DON'T DO NOTHIN'
TILL I COME BACK!

06:26.908 --> 06:29.737
-WHERE YOU GOIN'?
-STAY HERE!

06:29.867 --> 06:32.217
MS. GRIMES,
IT'S BREECE DOBBS CALLING YOU.

06:32.348 --> 06:33.654
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU
SOON AS I CAN.

06:33.784 --> 06:35.743
GOT A LITTLE SITUATION
BREWIN' HERE.

06:35.873 --> 06:39.137
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ] CALL ME
WHEN YOU CAN. THANK YOU.

06:39.268 --> 06:40.400
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
SHIT.

06:40.530 --> 06:42.967
-[ Man speaks indistinctly ]

06:43.098 --> 06:45.405
-[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]
-ANYTHING?

06:45.535 --> 06:47.537
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
-NO.

06:47.668 --> 06:49.452
NO, HIS PHONE'S STILL GOING
STRAIGHT TO VOICEMAIL.

06:49.583 --> 06:51.149
-YOU SAID HE WAS HEADED
INTO TOWN?

06:51.280 --> 06:54.239
-YEAH, UM, CALEB WANDERED OFF
THERE A COUPLE DAYS AGO.

06:54.370 --> 06:56.416
-WHY WOULD HE LEAVE
HIS TRUCK HERE?

06:56.546 --> 06:58.026
-YOU THINK MAYBE
HE FOUND CALEB HERE,

06:58.156 --> 06:59.767
THEN WENT FOR A HIKE
OR SOMETHIN'?

06:59.897 --> 07:02.465
-IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT?
-JUST THINKING OUT LOUD.

07:02.596 --> 07:03.945
-COME ON.
LET'S GO CHECK THE HOUSE.

07:04.075 --> 07:05.599
[ STATIC CRACKLES ]
-WE FOUND THE TRUCK.

07:05.729 --> 07:08.428
COUNTY ROAD 56,
NEAR THE GUN RANGE.

07:08.558 --> 07:10.473
WE'LL COME BACK FOR IT LATER.
[ STATIC CRACKLES ]

07:10.604 --> 07:12.040
LEDDA!

07:12.170 --> 07:15.130
♪♪

07:19.526 --> 07:22.398
-WADE?
-WADE?

07:22.529 --> 07:24.574
WADE? YOU THERE?

07:29.144 --> 07:31.189
[ GASPS ] CALEB!

07:31.320 --> 07:34.192
[ LAUGHS ] OH, MY GOD, CALEB!
YOU'RE SAFE.

07:34.323 --> 07:36.717
[ SNIFFLES ]
-WADE? YOU IN HERE?

07:36.847 --> 07:39.154
-[ LAUGHS ] WHERE DID YOU GO?

07:39.284 --> 07:41.025
-NOWHERE.
-WADE?

07:41.156 --> 07:42.636
-WELL, HOW DID YOU GET
BACK HERE?

07:42.766 --> 07:44.202
-I DON'T KNOW. I WALKED.

07:44.333 --> 07:45.856
-WHERE'S YOUR DAD?
DID HE NOT BRING YOU HERE?

07:45.987 --> 07:47.379
-WHERE'S HE AT, SON?
-I DON'T KNOW.

07:47.510 --> 07:49.338
AT WORK, I THINK.

07:49.469 --> 07:52.559
-CALEB, YOU WERE
SLEEPWALKING AGAIN.

07:52.689 --> 07:53.995
-OH.

07:54.125 --> 07:56.040
-AND YOUR DAD WENT
TO LOOK FOR YOU.

07:56.171 --> 07:58.303
-HE WASN'T HERE
WHEN I CAME BACK.

08:02.699 --> 08:04.484
-HE'S STILL OUT LOOKING FOR HIM.

08:04.614 --> 08:07.182
-WHERE, YOU THINK? AND WHY ISN'T
HE ANSWERING HIS PHONE?

08:07.312 --> 08:08.923
-I DON'T KNOW.

08:09.053 --> 08:11.752
-WELL, HE'S NOT IN THE HOUSE
OR THE GARAGE.

08:11.882 --> 08:13.493
CHECK THIS OUT.

08:17.845 --> 08:19.629
-[ SNIFFLES ]

08:19.760 --> 08:23.067
♪♪

08:38.822 --> 08:40.041
-[ SIGHS HEAVILY ]

08:40.171 --> 08:43.131
-[ GRUNTING ]

08:59.451 --> 09:00.844
-COME ON. COME ON.
-COME ON.

09:00.975 --> 09:03.151
-YOU AIN'T GONNA GET IT!
-COME ON, TAKE HIM.

09:03.281 --> 09:06.328
-HE CAN'T TAKE BOTH OF US!
HE CAN'T TAKE BOTH OF US!

09:06.458 --> 09:08.199
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING,
LAUGHTER IN DISTANCE ]

09:08.330 --> 09:09.549
[ POT CLATTERS ]

09:09.679 --> 09:12.987
-SOMETHING ABOUT
ASA FARRELL'S SOUL.

09:13.117 --> 09:16.120
IT'S DARK AS BURNT COAL.

09:16.251 --> 09:18.470
THAT WHY YOU LIKE HIM?

09:20.211 --> 09:22.779
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
-THAT WHAT DRAWS YOU IN ON HIM?

09:22.910 --> 09:24.476
'CAUSE HE GOT
A DEVIL INSIDE HIM?

09:24.607 --> 09:27.610
-I'M DRAWN
TO WHAT'S STRONG AND TRUE.

09:27.741 --> 09:29.830
BESIDES, ASA MEANS NOTHING
TO ME NOW.

09:29.960 --> 09:31.571
-[ CHUCKLES ]

09:31.701 --> 09:35.879
YOU SHOULDN'T LIE
TO YOUR FIANCé, YOU KNOW.

09:36.010 --> 09:38.142
DON'T BODE WELL
FOR THE RELATIONSHIP.

09:38.273 --> 09:42.930
I BELIEVE THAT YOU THINK
THAT YOU'RE DONE WITH HIM,

09:43.060 --> 09:45.585
BUT YOU AREN'T.

09:45.715 --> 09:48.762
I CAN SEE IT. MM-HMM.

09:48.892 --> 09:50.415
AND MY SON CAN SEE IT.

09:51.678 --> 09:53.680
WHEN THAT BOY,

09:53.810 --> 09:56.160
WHEN HE LEFT YOU...

09:56.291 --> 09:59.120
HE LEFT YOU WITHOUT A WORD.

09:59.250 --> 10:00.730
RIGHT?

10:00.861 --> 10:03.385
STANDING BY THE SIDE
OF THE ROAD.

10:03.515 --> 10:05.474
AND THAT WAS IT. GONE.

10:05.605 --> 10:07.781
SO...

10:10.000 --> 10:11.872
IT'S STILL INSIDE YOU.

10:14.178 --> 10:16.703
THAT FIRST LOVE.

10:16.833 --> 10:20.228
[ Whispers ]
IT'S RIGHT IN THERE.

10:20.358 --> 10:24.841
[ Normal voice ]
SO WHENEVER YOU SEE HIM...

10:24.972 --> 10:28.062
YOU'RE LIKE A GIRL AGAIN,

10:28.192 --> 10:33.110
STANDING BY A ROAD,
WATCHING YOUR HEART DISAPPEAR.

10:38.115 --> 10:40.161
I'M GONNA BANISH HIM

10:40.291 --> 10:43.077
FOR GOOD,

10:43.207 --> 10:45.209
AS SOON AS I GET MY GUNS.

10:45.340 --> 10:48.125
-I APPRECIATE THAT.

10:48.256 --> 10:50.432
BUT YOU'VE TRIED THAT BEFORE.

10:53.957 --> 10:56.177
THIS TIME, DON'T BANISH HIM.

10:57.874 --> 10:59.659
KILL HIM.

11:01.138 --> 11:03.793
-MM.

11:03.924 --> 11:06.666
THAT REALLY WHAT YOU WANT?

11:06.796 --> 11:08.885
OR...

11:09.016 --> 11:10.713
IS THIS SOME KIND OF GAME?
-BREN'IN?

11:10.844 --> 11:13.020
[ DOOR OPENS ]
-[ SIGHS ]

11:13.150 --> 11:15.631
I GOT YOUR SPECIAL BATCH
OF GINGER WINE, BREN'IN,

11:15.762 --> 11:17.285
RIGHT HERE.
[ OBJECTS CLATTER ]

11:17.415 --> 11:18.808
-HELL AND DAMNATION.

11:18.939 --> 11:21.506
[ ALL SPEAKING AT ONCE,
LAUGHTER ]

11:21.637 --> 11:23.770
-HEY THERE, FELLAS!
-[ CLEARS THROAT ]

11:23.900 --> 11:26.903
-WHEN I MADE YOU ALL
MY SENTRY WARDS,

11:27.034 --> 11:32.169
I SAID I WANT MY BEST MEN
FOR THE JOB.

11:32.300 --> 11:35.564
DID I GET MY BEST MEN? NO.

11:35.695 --> 11:39.699
I GOT BOYS WHO ARE PLAYIN'!

11:39.829 --> 11:43.267
WELL, I DON'T NEED
BOYS PLAYIN'.

11:43.398 --> 11:45.487
-WELL, FOSTER, WE WAS JUST
HAVING A LITTLE FUN AND --

11:45.617 --> 11:47.707
AAH! UHH!

11:47.837 --> 11:50.448
[ GROANING AND GASPING ]

11:50.579 --> 11:53.103
AAH! UHH!

11:53.234 --> 11:55.149
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

11:55.279 --> 11:57.934
-NOW...

11:58.065 --> 12:01.198
MAYBE YOU'LL REMEMBER
WHEN I TELL YOU SOMETHING.

12:02.939 --> 12:04.245
ANYBODY...

12:04.375 --> 12:05.637
-[ GROANS ]

12:05.768 --> 12:07.944
-ANYBODY COME UP HERE

12:08.075 --> 12:10.642
THAT MIGHT HAVE FIRE ON THEM --

12:10.773 --> 12:14.690
AND I DON'T WANT YOU THINKIN'!

12:14.821 --> 12:16.170
I WANT YOU SHOOTIN'!

12:16.300 --> 12:19.390
-[ GRUNTING AND GROANING ]

12:19.521 --> 12:21.001
-YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

12:21.131 --> 12:25.005
-[ GROANING CONTINUES ]

12:25.135 --> 12:27.529
THAT SOUNDS LIKE A "YES" TO ME.

12:27.659 --> 12:30.488
-[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

12:30.619 --> 12:32.621
♪♪

12:32.752 --> 12:34.275
-[ GROANING CONTINUES ]

12:34.405 --> 12:38.627
[ PANTING ]

12:44.067 --> 12:47.636
-[ SCREAMS AND GROANS ]

12:47.767 --> 12:50.770
[ GRUNTING ]

12:50.900 --> 12:52.684
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

12:52.815 --> 12:55.252
AM I EVER GONNA WALK AGAIN?

12:55.383 --> 12:57.341
-YES, JUST NOT FOR A FEW DAYS.

12:57.472 --> 13:00.649
-BOTH LEGS NOW?!
I DON'T WANNA BE A CRIPPLE.

13:00.780 --> 13:02.999
-SETTLE DOWN.
HE JUST GRAZED YOU.

13:03.130 --> 13:06.394
-[ INHALING SHARPLY ]

13:06.524 --> 13:07.743
-COME HERE.

13:10.877 --> 13:13.183
IN CASE YOU BOYS
DIDN'T GET THE MESSAGE,

13:13.314 --> 13:15.011
THINGS ARE A LITTLE DIFFERENT
AROUND HERE NOW.

13:15.142 --> 13:16.665
-[ Whispers ] YES, MA'AM.

13:16.796 --> 13:18.536
-AND I DON'T WANT ANYONE ELSE
GETTING HURT. ALL RIGHT?

13:18.667 --> 13:19.886
-I HEAR THAT.

13:23.193 --> 13:25.848
-SO I'M GONNA NEED YOUR HELP.

13:25.979 --> 13:28.329
WE ALL NEED YOUR HELP.

13:28.459 --> 13:30.810
YOU WITH ME?

13:30.940 --> 13:33.334
-YEAH.

13:33.464 --> 13:34.901
-YES, MA'AM.

13:43.039 --> 13:45.912
-[ SCREAMING ]

13:46.042 --> 13:49.437
-ALL RIGHT, BUDDY.

13:49.567 --> 13:51.569
AND YOU LET US KNOW THE SECOND
YOU HEAR FROM HIM, ALL RIGHT?

13:51.700 --> 13:54.355
-YEAH, I WILL.
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

13:54.485 --> 13:56.226
HEY, FULTS.

13:56.357 --> 13:57.880
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:58.011 --> 14:00.187
LISTEN, UH...

14:00.317 --> 14:05.409
WADE'S BEEN FALLING
FOR SUCH A LONG TIME, AND...

14:05.540 --> 14:08.238
I CAN'T PRETEND THAT I'M
COMPLETELY SURPRISED BY THIS.

14:08.369 --> 14:10.588
BUT...

14:10.719 --> 14:12.852
HE WOULD NEVER DO THAT
TO CALEB, RIGHT?

14:12.982 --> 14:15.115
-W-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

14:15.245 --> 14:16.856
-WADE'S WIFE.

14:16.986 --> 14:19.728
UH, THEY FOUND
HER CAR ABANDONED

14:19.859 --> 14:22.600
ON THE NIGHT THAT SHE JUMPED
OFF THE BRIDGE,

14:22.731 --> 14:24.472
AND THEY NEVER FOUND HER BODY.

14:24.602 --> 14:26.039
-YEAH, HE AND I HAVE NEVER
DISCUSSED IT.

14:26.169 --> 14:28.650
BUT, I MEAN, THERE'S RUMORS
AROUND TOWN, BUT...

14:28.780 --> 14:33.263
-ANDI-RAE WAS, UH,
SHE WAS A SWEET THING.

14:33.394 --> 14:37.137
SHE WAS A RAY OF SUNSHINE,
TILL SHE WASN'T.

14:39.008 --> 14:41.184
AFTER IT HAPPENED,

14:41.315 --> 14:43.056
UH, WADE JUST
KIND OF WANDERED AROUND

14:43.186 --> 14:45.014
LIKE HE WAS A GHOST.

14:45.145 --> 14:47.408
YOU KNOW...

14:47.538 --> 14:49.540
I DON'T KNOW,
MAYBE HE FINALLY DECIDED

14:49.671 --> 14:52.456
THAT HE'D JUST BECOME ONE.

15:01.944 --> 15:03.076
[ DOOR OPENS ]

15:03.206 --> 15:06.993
♪♪

15:07.123 --> 15:10.474
-DON'T GIVE A TINKER'S DAMN
IF BIG FOSTER GAVE HIS APPROVAL.

15:10.605 --> 15:13.129
I DISTRIBUTE LIBATIONS HERE,
TO US.

15:13.260 --> 15:15.088
-I REALIZE
IT'S AN UNUSUAL REQUEST.

15:15.218 --> 15:17.003
-UNUSUAL AND UNWISE.

15:17.133 --> 15:20.484
I ONLY GAVE YOU THAT LAST JUG
SO AS TO SAVE YOUR LIFE.

15:20.615 --> 15:23.574
AND WHAT, I MAY ASK, DID I GET
FOR THAT VOUCHSAFEMENT?

15:23.705 --> 15:25.750
YOU GIVE A MIGHTY WEAPON
TO A MADMAN.

15:25.881 --> 15:27.839
-LOOK, IT'S ALL PART
OF A LARGER PLAN, KRAKE.

15:27.970 --> 15:29.929
-I WAS STANDING THERE.

15:30.059 --> 15:31.931
HE SHOT ENOCH IN THE LEG.

15:32.061 --> 15:34.934
HE DONE THAT WITH ONEGUN,
AND YOU WANNA GIVE HIM MORE?

15:35.064 --> 15:36.500
IT'S LUNACY.

15:36.631 --> 15:38.850
-[ SCOFFS ] OKAY. LOOK.

15:38.981 --> 15:40.722
I GIVE YOU MY WORD.

15:40.852 --> 15:42.898
I PROMISED FOSTER
A HUNDRED GUNS.

15:43.029 --> 15:44.508
HE'LL NEVER SEE
A SINGLE ONE OF 'EM.

15:44.639 --> 15:46.641
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE ME.

15:46.771 --> 15:47.947
-WHY?

15:48.077 --> 15:50.253
PARTICULARS DON'T MAKE NO SENSE.

15:50.384 --> 15:52.212
GIVING GUNS TO BIG FOSTER,

15:52.342 --> 15:55.650
OBTAINING 'EM BY TRADING AWAY
OUR NECTAR, OUR BLESSED WINE,

15:55.780 --> 15:57.478
DOWN THERE TO THEM?

15:57.608 --> 15:59.132
HOW CAN I TRUST YOU, COUSIN?

15:59.262 --> 16:00.960
YOU SAY YOU'RE LYING
TO BIG FOSTER.

16:01.090 --> 16:03.266
HOW I KNOW YOU'RE NOT ALSO
LYIN' TO ME?

16:03.397 --> 16:05.094
-YOU'RE RIGHT.
WE'RE TRUTH TELLERS.

16:05.225 --> 16:06.835
ALWAYS HAVE BEEN.

16:06.966 --> 16:10.273
BUT, KRAKE, THESE TIMES,
EXCEPTIONS ARE THE RULE.

16:10.404 --> 16:12.710
BIG FOSTER'S GONNA GET
THOSE GUNS ONE WAY OR THE OTHER.

16:12.841 --> 16:15.452
SO IF YOU GOT A BETTER IDEA,
TELL ME NOW, COUSIN,

16:15.583 --> 16:18.064
'CAUSE WE'RE RUNNING OUT
OF TIME, AND I NEED YOUR HELP.

16:18.194 --> 16:20.805
[ LIQUID BUBBLING ]

16:29.423 --> 16:30.815
THANK YOU.

16:33.993 --> 16:35.820
I SHALL RETURN.

16:47.310 --> 16:49.617
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

16:49.747 --> 16:51.271
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

16:51.401 --> 16:53.490
[ TOOLBOX THUDS ]

16:53.621 --> 16:56.580
[ CLATTERING ]

16:58.147 --> 17:00.671
-COUSIN PHIL'UP.

17:00.802 --> 17:02.325
-MA'AM.

17:02.456 --> 17:04.066
-GET IN HERE.

17:06.721 --> 17:08.027
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

17:08.157 --> 17:09.593
YOU FOLLOWING ME?

17:09.724 --> 17:11.378
-I'M JUST WATCHIN', MA'AM.

17:11.508 --> 17:13.162
-WATCHIN' WHAT?

17:13.293 --> 17:14.642
-YOU.

17:17.253 --> 17:19.603
-WATCHIN' ME?

17:21.083 --> 17:23.999
WHY?
-UH, BREN'IN TOLD ME TO.

17:24.130 --> 17:26.219
SAID IT WAS FOR YOUR PROTECTION.

17:26.349 --> 17:28.873
-IS THAT RIGHT?
WELL, I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

17:29.004 --> 17:31.311
SO WHY DON'T YOU GO TELL
THE BREN'IN THAT?

17:31.441 --> 17:33.661
-I CAN'T DO THAT.

17:33.791 --> 17:35.793
HE SAID I GOTTA
STAY WITH YOU, SO --

17:35.924 --> 17:38.448
-PHIL'UP. MM-HMM.
-I'M -- I'M GONNA GO. I'M GOING.

17:38.579 --> 17:40.276
I'M... [ CLEARS THROAT ]

17:40.407 --> 17:43.627
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

17:43.758 --> 17:47.196
-SOME FOLKS SAY HE KILLED HER.
HOUGHTON.

17:47.327 --> 17:49.938
DROVE HER CAR TO THE BRIDGE
TO MAKE IT LOOK LIKE A SUICIDE.

17:50.069 --> 17:51.853
THAT'S WHY THEY COULDN'T FIND
THE BODY.

17:51.983 --> 17:53.985
-YOU GOT ANY EVIDENCE OF THAT?

17:54.116 --> 17:57.250
'CAUSE IF YOU DON'T,
SHUT YOUR DAMN PIE HOLE.

17:57.380 --> 17:58.903
[ SIGHS ]

17:59.034 --> 18:00.557
GONNA HAVE TO DRAG IT, I GUESS.

18:00.688 --> 18:03.778
-AW, MAN. WE HAD TO DRAG
THE LAKE BEFORE YOU CAME.

18:03.908 --> 18:06.737
COST $50,000.
AND IT WAS A SMALL LAKE.

18:06.868 --> 18:08.783
-WHAT DO YOU CARE?
IT'S TAXPAYERS' MONEY.

18:10.132 --> 18:12.352
-DIDN'T GET A RAISE THAT YEAR.

18:12.482 --> 18:15.485
I'M JUST SAYIN'.
-HE'S ONE OF OUR OWN, DOLAN.

18:17.357 --> 18:18.836
I'LL ORDER THE DRAG.

18:18.967 --> 18:21.622
-[ SIGHS ]

18:21.752 --> 18:23.319
♪♪

18:23.450 --> 18:26.496
-[ GRUNTING ]

18:38.291 --> 18:40.684
[ PANTING ]

19:09.017 --> 19:11.759
[ ROCKS AND GRAVEL CRUMBLING ]

19:11.889 --> 19:14.675
UHH!

19:14.805 --> 19:17.417
[ CONTINUES GRUNTING ]

19:19.114 --> 19:22.204
[ PANTING ]

19:27.427 --> 19:29.733
[ CONTINUES PANTING ]

19:29.864 --> 19:35.348
AH! AH! AH! AH!
[ PANTING ]

19:35.478 --> 19:38.612
OH, GOD. OH, GOD, NO.
NO. PLEASE!

19:38.742 --> 19:40.048
NO!
[ TAPPING ]

19:45.314 --> 19:47.795
-JUST CAN'T GO AROUND SHOOTIN'
PEOPLE IS ALL I'M SAYING.

19:47.925 --> 19:51.190
-HMM. SO IT'S ALL RIGHT FOR ME
TO KILL ASA.

19:51.320 --> 19:53.235
THAT'S OKAY.

19:53.366 --> 19:54.845
BUT TEACHING THAT FIDDLEHEAD
A LESSON,

19:54.976 --> 19:57.457
THAT'S NOT BREN'IN OF ME?

19:57.587 --> 20:00.982
-YOU CAN TEACH PEOPLE
WITHOUT HARMING THEM, FOSTER.

20:01.112 --> 20:02.723
-DON'T CUT IT TOO CLOSE.

20:02.853 --> 20:04.855
I LIKE THEM FRUIT FLIES
HAVE A PLACE TO HIDE.

20:07.554 --> 20:09.860
-YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY, YOU
TRUSTING ME WITH THESE POINTS

20:09.991 --> 20:11.253
SO CLOSE TO YOUR THROAT,

20:11.384 --> 20:13.299
BUT YOU DON'T TRUST ME
OTHERWISE.

20:13.429 --> 20:17.085
WORD'S GOTTEN OUT THAT
YOU SHOT ENOCH FOR PLAYING DICE.

20:17.216 --> 20:19.957
NOW YOU GOT PEOPLE SCARED.

20:20.088 --> 20:22.743
THAT'S NOT
HOW YOU LEAD RIGHTLY.

20:22.873 --> 20:26.094
-KRAKE. HE'S THE SAUCE-BOX
BLABBERED EVERYWHERE, AIN'T HE?

20:26.225 --> 20:28.009
-NO, I DON'T THINK HE DID.

20:28.139 --> 20:30.359
-IT WAS ENOCH.
-MAYBE IT WAS ME.

20:35.973 --> 20:37.236
FOSTER...

20:41.849 --> 20:44.068
-WHEN I GOT REASON
TO TRUST YOU...

20:49.335 --> 20:50.597
I WILL.

20:57.560 --> 21:00.650
[ CLINKING ]

21:00.781 --> 21:02.391
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

21:08.354 --> 21:09.616
-HASIL?

21:21.628 --> 21:23.760
UHH! [ GROANS ]

21:23.891 --> 21:26.285
-GET OUT OF MY HOUSE,
OR I'M GONNA START SCREAMIN'!

21:26.415 --> 21:28.852
-LISTEN, IT'S ASA FARRELL.
I'M A FRIEND OF HASIL'S.

21:28.983 --> 21:31.290
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
GODDAMN.

21:31.420 --> 21:35.076
HE TOLD ME ABOUT THIS PLACE,
SAID I COULD FIND HIM HERE.

21:35.206 --> 21:37.992
HI. [ PANTING ]

21:38.122 --> 21:41.430
YOU'RE, UH,
YOU'RE SALLY-ANN, RIGHT?

21:41.561 --> 21:43.824
MAN, HE'S TOLD ME SO MUCH
ABOUT YOU.

21:43.954 --> 21:45.129
-WHAT DO YOU WANT?

21:45.260 --> 21:46.870
-I JUST WANT SOME FRUIT JUGS.

21:47.001 --> 21:49.308
HASIL AND I ARE GOING
INTO BUSINESS.

21:51.397 --> 21:54.617
-SO, HOW WELL YOU KNOW HASIL?

21:55.879 --> 21:59.230
-NOT AS WELL AS I SHOULD.

21:59.361 --> 22:02.321
I WAS AWAY FROM THE MOUNTAIN
FOR A SPELL.

22:02.451 --> 22:04.540
-YOU WERE? WHY?

22:04.671 --> 22:08.849
-YOU KNOW, SEE THE WORLD.
YOU KNOW, THAT KIND OF THING.

22:08.979 --> 22:13.114
YOU'VE LIVED, UH, YOU'VE LIVED
HERE YOUR WHOLE LIFE, RIGHT?

22:13.244 --> 22:16.509
-SAVING UP MY PENNIES, THOUGH,
TO GO...

22:16.639 --> 22:19.512
I DON'T KNOW. WHEREVER.

22:19.642 --> 22:21.862
-IS THAT WHAT YOU NEED HIM FOR?

22:23.124 --> 22:26.649
LIKE HE'S YOUR TICKET
OUT OF HERE?

22:26.780 --> 22:29.826
I HATE TO BREAK IT TO YOU,
BUT...

22:29.957 --> 22:32.568
HE'S NEVER HAD MUCH LUCK
WITH MONEY.

22:32.699 --> 22:35.484
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

22:35.615 --> 22:39.488
-HOW'D YOU THINK HE LOST
THOSE FINGERS?

22:39.619 --> 22:42.491
I MEAN, WE GOT SOME
PRETTY SEVERE RULES UP THERE.

22:42.622 --> 22:45.494
-[ SCOFFS ] ARE YOU SERIOUS?

22:48.541 --> 22:50.020
-LOOK...

22:53.415 --> 22:55.852
YOU SEEM LIKE A REAL NICE GIRL,

22:55.983 --> 22:58.464
BUT YOU REALLY GOTTA LOOK OUT
FOR YOURSELF.

22:58.594 --> 23:00.988
YOU UNDERSTAND?

23:01.118 --> 23:04.861
YOU GOTTA LOOK OUT FOR HIM, TOO,
'CAUSE HE'S NEW TO ALL OF THIS.

23:04.992 --> 23:07.560
-[ GASPS, SNIFFLES ]

23:07.690 --> 23:09.388
NEW TO ALL WHAT?

23:09.518 --> 23:13.174
-THE GLORIES OF CIVILIZATION.

23:16.133 --> 23:17.700
-[ SNIFFLES ]

23:17.831 --> 23:19.441
[ LID CLATTERS ]

23:20.747 --> 23:23.184
[ DOOR CREAKS ]
-[ SIGHS ]

23:23.314 --> 23:24.620
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

23:26.100 --> 23:27.536
-WHERE IS HE?

23:28.929 --> 23:30.321
-DOWN THE BASEMENT.

23:30.452 --> 23:31.932
-ALL RIGHT,
I'M GONNA TALK TO HIM ALONE.

23:32.062 --> 23:33.716
BEFORE I DO,
WHAT DO WE KNOW ABOUT HIM?

23:33.847 --> 23:35.283
-WHAT'S TO KNOW? HE'S AN ANIMAL.

23:35.414 --> 23:37.764
-AND HE'S, UH, MISSING ONE-HALF
OF ONE HAND.

23:37.894 --> 23:39.635
-AND DOES THE ANIMAL
HAVE A NAME?

23:39.766 --> 23:41.855
OR DIDN'T YOU FIND THAT OUT
BEFORE YOU STARTED BEATING HIM?

23:41.985 --> 23:44.466
-IT'S HAZZLE. OR HAYZIL.

23:44.597 --> 23:46.207
SOMETHING.

23:46.337 --> 23:48.296
I MET HIM ONCE BEFORE
WHEN HE CAME AFTER MY SISTER.

23:48.427 --> 23:50.690
-AND WHAT'S HER NAME?

23:50.820 --> 23:53.562
-SALLY-ANN.

24:10.361 --> 24:11.624
-GOOD AFTERNOON.

24:11.754 --> 24:13.190
HAZZLE, IS IT?

24:13.321 --> 24:15.018
MY NAME'S HAYLIE GRIMES.

24:15.149 --> 24:16.542
HOW YOU FEELIN'?

24:18.674 --> 24:20.589
-FA!

24:20.720 --> 24:22.635
-FOSTER, STOP.

24:22.765 --> 24:25.028
-FA!
-STAY RIGHT THERE!

24:25.159 --> 24:26.508
-YOU HEARD HIM, FOSTER.

24:26.639 --> 24:30.033
WE GOT ORDERS TO SHOOT.
-WELL, GO ON!

24:30.164 --> 24:32.471
DO IT THEN. SHOOT ME.

24:32.601 --> 24:33.994
[ GUNSHOT ]

24:34.124 --> 24:36.300
-STOP. I DON'T WANNA SHOOT YOU.

24:36.431 --> 24:37.650
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:37.780 --> 24:39.826
-WHAT THE HELL
IS THIS RUCKUS ABOUT?!

24:39.956 --> 24:41.349
-HE WANTS US TO SHOOT HIM.

24:41.480 --> 24:43.569
-SO WHY DIDN'T YOU?
HE GOT A GUN, DON'T HE?

24:43.699 --> 24:46.441
-YEAH, BUT --
-YEAH, BUT WHAT?

24:46.572 --> 24:48.269
-WELL, HE'S YOUR BOY.
-OH, HE'S MY BOY.

24:48.399 --> 24:50.532
I GAVE YOU ORDERS.
ANYBODY COME HERE WITH A GUN,

24:50.663 --> 24:52.186
YOU SHOOT THEM!
-HEY, HEY, HEY!

24:52.316 --> 24:54.580
DON'T YOU SHOOT HIM!
YOU SHOOT ME.

24:54.710 --> 24:56.146
HUH?

24:56.277 --> 24:59.280
YOU TOOK EVERYTHING FROM ME.

24:59.410 --> 25:01.021
GO ON.

25:01.151 --> 25:03.763
SO FINISH WHAT YOU STARTED
THE DAY I WAS BORN.

25:03.893 --> 25:05.591
KILL ME.

25:05.721 --> 25:08.158
-NO. IT AIN'T WORTH KILLING YOU.

25:08.289 --> 25:10.204
YOU'RE MORE THAN HALF-DEAD
ALREADY.

25:10.334 --> 25:12.989
YOU WANNA GET KILLED?
YOU GO DO IT TO YOURSELF!

25:14.817 --> 25:16.123
[ GRUNTING ]
-I'M YOUR SON.

25:16.253 --> 25:17.733
-GET OFF ME!
-I'M YOUR SON.

25:17.864 --> 25:19.518
-GET OFF ME!
-I'M YOUR SON!

25:19.648 --> 25:22.869
[ GRUNTING CONTINUES ]

25:22.999 --> 25:27.526
-[ PANTING ] NOW YOU GO GET
YOURSELF STRAIGHT.

25:27.656 --> 25:31.704
I AIN'T NEVER SEEN YOU SUCH
A PATHETIC MESS IN ALL MY LIFE.

25:34.533 --> 25:37.666
♪♪

25:41.714 --> 25:43.106
YOU GONNA SHOOT ME?

25:43.237 --> 25:45.848
-[ PANTING ]

25:45.979 --> 25:48.721
-GO AHEAD AND DO IT.

25:59.427 --> 26:01.908
NO, NO...

26:02.038 --> 26:03.953
-AAH! AH!

26:04.084 --> 26:06.390
[ GRUNTING ]

26:06.521 --> 26:09.393
-LIL. NO. HEY.
[ GUN CLATTERS ]

26:09.524 --> 26:12.483
-[ PANTING ]

26:22.929 --> 26:26.193
[ MEN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE,
GUNSHOTS ]

26:26.323 --> 26:27.629
[ CLICK ]

26:27.760 --> 26:29.718
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:29.849 --> 26:31.981
-ROLL, ROLL, ALL THE WAY DOWN.

26:32.112 --> 26:35.724
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS,
GUNSHOTS CONTINUE ]

26:37.813 --> 26:40.076
-HOW'S IT GOING, SOLDIER?

26:40.207 --> 26:43.210
UH, I'M DONNIE.
I'M A FRIEND OF ABEL'S.

26:43.340 --> 26:45.647
[ GUNSHOTS ]
-LET 'EM PASS!

26:45.778 --> 26:47.083
-[ In distance ] WAIT. CLEAR!

26:47.214 --> 26:50.304
[ GATE CREAKS ]

26:50.434 --> 26:51.958
-THANK YOU, SOLDIER.

26:52.088 --> 26:54.264
OLD ABEL'S GOOD PEOPLE.

26:54.395 --> 26:56.745
I USUALLY SEE HIM
AT RE-ENACTMENTS.

26:56.876 --> 26:59.835
BUT I AM CAPTAIN
JUBEL T. ARLINGTON, C.S.A.

26:59.966 --> 27:01.402
HE USUALLY PLAYS
STONEWALL JACKSON.

27:01.532 --> 27:03.230
-OH, YEAH?

27:03.360 --> 27:06.146
IS THAT BEFORE OR AFTER HIS OWN
MEN SHOT HIM OFF HIS HORSE?

27:06.276 --> 27:09.149
[ RAPID GUNFIRE ]

27:10.716 --> 27:12.631
-YOU BETTER LET ME DO
THE TALKING.

27:12.761 --> 27:14.154
[ CHUCKLES ] HEY.

27:14.284 --> 27:16.765
MY FRIEND AND I COME BY
TO DO SOME MORE BUSINESS.

27:16.896 --> 27:18.201
SWAP YOU
MORE OF OUR FARRELL WINE

27:18.332 --> 27:19.463
FOR SOME OF YOUR FINE WEAPONRY.

27:19.594 --> 27:21.030
-THAT DEAL WAS A ONE-OFF, MAN.

27:21.161 --> 27:22.858
-OH, COME ON NOW, ABEL.
TELL ME TRUE.

27:22.989 --> 27:24.991
WASN'T THAT THE FINEST SHINE
YOU EVER SIPPED?

27:25.121 --> 27:27.167
-[ SIGHS ] NO ARGUMENT THERE.
-YEAH.

27:27.297 --> 27:29.735
[ MACHINE GUNFIRE CONTINUES ]

27:29.865 --> 27:31.606
-[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
-[ LAUGHS ]

27:31.737 --> 27:34.653
-I PLAYED "CALL OF DUTY" FOR
29 HOURS STRAIGHT ON THAT SHIT.

27:34.783 --> 27:37.873
I GOT 8 GOLD CAMOS
AND 44 KILL STREAKS.

27:38.004 --> 27:40.571
BUT WE AIN'T RUNNING A GODDAMN
LIQUOR STORE HERE, DONNIE.

27:40.702 --> 27:44.401
I GOT ENOUGH TROUBLE
WITH THE FEDS AS IT IS. SORRY.

27:44.532 --> 27:46.882
-OKAY, WAIT. HEY.
[ BOTTLES CLANK ]

27:47.013 --> 27:50.016
THIS HERE FELLA IS A FARRELL.
A FARRELL.

27:50.146 --> 27:51.844
THE REAL FIRST FAMILY
OF AMERICA!

27:51.974 --> 27:53.454
THEY ARE OFF THE GRID,

27:53.584 --> 27:55.412
THESE PEOPLE,
UNTOUCHED BY THE GOVERNMENT.

27:55.543 --> 27:57.719
THEY DON'T BELIEVE IN MONEY,
MUCH LESS THE FEDERAL RESERVE.

27:57.850 --> 28:00.722
THIS MAN IS A HERO.

28:00.853 --> 28:03.682
-I RELATE TO YOUR STRUGGLE,
BROTHER.

28:03.812 --> 28:05.684
TELL YOU WHAT.

28:05.814 --> 28:08.512
YOU WANNA PURCHASE
MORE FIREARMS, BRING ME CASH.

28:08.643 --> 28:10.340
-SHIT, I WAS HOPING
WE COULD USE BITCOIN.

28:13.082 --> 28:17.173
-[ LAUGHING ] YOU'RE FUNNY.

28:17.304 --> 28:18.522
-HUH.

28:20.176 --> 28:22.004
-CASH WORKS FINE.

28:23.919 --> 28:26.313
[ GUNFIRE CONTINUES ]

28:26.443 --> 28:28.271
-I TOLD YOU,
LET ME DO THE TALKING.

28:28.402 --> 28:31.100
-I BARELY SAID TWO WORDS.
-WELL, WE'RE RIGHT SCREWED NOW.

28:31.231 --> 28:34.364
-OKAY, JUST HOW YOU FIGURE?
-I DONE ALL I CAN FOR YOU HERE.

28:34.495 --> 28:36.671
-LOOK, HOW MANY CUSTOMERS
YOU GET AT THE STORE PER DAY?

28:36.802 --> 28:39.282
FOR REAL.
-TYPICAL DAY, 5 OR 6.

28:39.413 --> 28:42.285
BUT IT'S A HOBBY SHOP,
MEANING IT'S MY HOBBY.

28:42.416 --> 28:45.201
REAL BUSINESS IS DONE ONLINE
THESE DAYS.

28:45.332 --> 28:48.030
-OKAY, NOW YOU SAY YOU GOT
CUSTOMER GENERATION ONLINE,

28:48.161 --> 28:49.858
YOU GOT BRICK AND MORTAR.

28:49.989 --> 28:52.121
SOUNDS LIKE
A PRETTY SOLID BUSINESS PLAN.

28:52.252 --> 28:54.254
-WHAT ARE YOU SAYIN', EXACTLY?

28:54.384 --> 28:56.299
I'M SAYING, DON'T YOU THINK
THE PEOPLE OF THIS TOWN

28:56.430 --> 28:57.779
NEED A NEW HOBBY?

28:57.910 --> 28:59.259
[ MACHINE GUNFIRE CONTINUES
IN DISTANCE ]

28:59.389 --> 29:01.174
WHAT KIND OF CUT YOU WANT?

29:02.697 --> 29:03.872
-GET TO WORK, BROTHER.

29:04.003 --> 29:05.700
-THOUGHT SO.

29:05.831 --> 29:07.963
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

29:08.094 --> 29:10.313
-LOOK, I DON'T KNOW THESE MEN,

29:10.444 --> 29:13.708
BUT THEY'VE DONE
A TERRIBLE THING.

29:13.839 --> 29:16.711
AND I GIVE YOU PROMISE THAT
IT WILL NOT STAND.

29:16.842 --> 29:18.931
-YOU WITH THE POLICE?

29:19.061 --> 29:20.628
YOU GONNA ARREST THEM?

29:20.759 --> 29:22.761
-NOT EXACTLY.

29:22.891 --> 29:24.197
BUT I AM HERE TO HELP YOU.

29:24.327 --> 29:26.068
-WELL, KILLING 'EM
MIGHT HELP ME.

29:26.199 --> 29:29.376
OR MAYBE YOU CAN JUST SET ME
LOOSE AND I CAN DO IT MYSELF.

29:29.506 --> 29:32.814
-WELL, I AM HERE TO --
TO SET YOU FREE

29:32.945 --> 29:35.904
AND TO OFFER YOU A JOB,
I MIGHT ADD.

29:36.035 --> 29:38.646
LET ME JUST SHOW YOU SOMETHIN'.

29:38.777 --> 29:41.997
NOW THERE'S NO OFFICIAL NAME
FOR THE DEVELOPMENT YET,

29:42.128 --> 29:44.521
BUT I'M THINKIN'...

29:44.652 --> 29:46.567
SHAY MOUNTAIN CROSSING.

29:46.697 --> 29:49.178
SOMETHING ALONG THOSE LINES.

29:49.309 --> 29:51.833
IT IS 1 TO 3 BEDROOMS,

29:51.964 --> 29:56.229
ALL NEW APPLIANCES, CARPETING,
DUAL FLUSH ECO-FRIENDLY TOILET,

29:56.359 --> 29:58.709
AND A STATE-OF-THE-ART
SECURITY SYSTEM.

30:02.061 --> 30:03.584
WELL, I KNOW IT MAY NOT
INTEREST YOU,

30:03.714 --> 30:06.021
BUT I WAS THINKING
IT MIGHT SALLY-ANN.

30:06.152 --> 30:10.373
SHE COULD USE A-A NEW HOME,
DON'T YOU THINK?

30:10.504 --> 30:13.463
-SO, WHAT, YOU JUST GONNA LET US
LIVE IN THAT HOUSE RIGHT THERE?

30:13.594 --> 30:15.552
-IT COMES FREE WITH THE JOB,
YES.

30:15.683 --> 30:17.293
-WHICH IS WHAT?
-LIAISON.

30:17.424 --> 30:19.774
-BETWEEN?
-BETWEEN YOU AND YOUR FAMILY.

30:19.905 --> 30:21.602
ALL YOU WOULD HAVE TO DO
IS SPREAD THE WORD

30:21.732 --> 30:23.343
BETWEEN YOU AND YOUR KIN
UP ON YOUR HILL.

30:23.473 --> 30:25.475
-WORD ABOUT WHAT?

30:25.606 --> 30:28.957
-OH, WE'RE BUILDING 20 CONDOS,
JUST LIKE THIS ONE.

30:29.088 --> 30:31.220
JUST FOR YOU AND YOUR FAMILY.

30:31.351 --> 30:34.397
AND EACH ONE WOULD BE 100% FREE
TO ANY FAMILY OF FOUR OR MORE

30:34.528 --> 30:35.834
THAT WANTS TO MOVE IN.

30:35.964 --> 30:37.966
-HOW MUCH IS IT GONNA PAY?

30:38.097 --> 30:40.882
-WELL, YOU WOULD GET
THE PLACE TO LIVE.

30:41.013 --> 30:42.405
-[ LAUGHS ]

30:42.536 --> 30:45.147
LADY, I ALREADY GOT ME
A PLACE TO LIVE.

30:48.629 --> 30:51.110
-OKAY.

30:51.240 --> 30:53.939
HOW ABOUT A STARTING SALARY
OF $200 A WEEK?

30:54.069 --> 30:56.463
-HOW ABOUT YOU MAKE IT
$1,000 A WEEK?

30:57.943 --> 30:59.683
AND YOU PAY ME RIGHT NOW.

31:04.514 --> 31:07.126
-WELCOME TO THE TEAM.

31:09.041 --> 31:12.609
[ Whispers ]
LET'S GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

31:12.740 --> 31:14.046
-HEY, UH,

31:14.176 --> 31:16.570
THE "BATTLESTAR GALACTICA"
MODEL'S A HONEY.

31:16.700 --> 31:19.051
-I'M "STAR TREK" ONLY.
-I KNOW THAT, TOM.

31:19.181 --> 31:21.967
I'M JUST TRYING TO TEMPT YOU
INTO GREENER PASTURES, IS ALL.

31:22.097 --> 31:24.447
SPEAKING OF WHICH, UH...

31:24.578 --> 31:26.232
I GOT SOMETHING THAT'LL MAKE
A WARP DRIVE

31:26.362 --> 31:27.929
LOOK LIKE AN '85 PINTO.

31:28.060 --> 31:30.758
GENUINE FARRELL WINE.

31:30.889 --> 31:32.455
-NO SHIT.

31:32.586 --> 31:34.588
-BEST SHINE
IN THE STATE OF KENTUCKY.

31:34.718 --> 31:36.677
-YEAH, I HEARD TELL OF IT
FOR YEARS.

31:36.807 --> 31:39.201
-WELL, MY OLD FAMILY RECIPE
BEATS ALL.

31:39.332 --> 31:40.855
-YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

31:40.986 --> 31:42.857
[ THE ABIGAILS' "TWENTY NINE"
PLAYING ]

31:42.988 --> 31:46.208
WHY DON'T YOU TRY A TUG?
FREE OF CHARGE.

31:46.339 --> 31:48.036
[ LID CLATTERS ]

31:48.167 --> 31:50.996
♪♪

31:52.562 --> 31:56.610
-[ LAUGHING ] SHIT FIRE
AND SAVE THE MATCH!

31:56.740 --> 31:58.307
THAT WENT DOWN SMOOTHER
THAN SILK!

31:58.438 --> 31:59.961
-SEE?
-HOW MUCH?

32:00.092 --> 32:03.791
-$80 FOR REGULAR FOLK.
$60 FOR FAMILY AND FRIENDS.

32:03.922 --> 32:05.706
-HELL...

32:05.836 --> 32:08.187
BLESS YOU, DONNIE.

32:08.317 --> 32:10.929
-MORE WHERE THAT CAME FROM.

32:11.059 --> 32:12.626
TELL YOUR FRIENDS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:12.756 --> 32:15.237
-[ LAUGHS ]
-TAKE IT EASY, TOM.

32:15.368 --> 32:16.804
[ DOOR BELLS JINGLE ]

32:16.935 --> 32:20.155
♪♪

32:20.286 --> 32:21.940
-GIVE ME A TASTE, DONNIE?

32:22.070 --> 32:24.943
[ JAR CLATTERS ]

32:25.073 --> 32:27.946
♪♪

32:28.076 --> 32:30.339
-[ SLURPS ]

32:30.470 --> 32:31.819
[ GULPS ] HMM.

32:31.950 --> 32:33.995
IS IT SUNDAY?
-[ CHUCKLES ]

32:34.126 --> 32:36.432
-'CAUSE I FEEL LIKE I'M
IN THE HOUSE OF THE LORD GOD.

32:36.563 --> 32:39.000
-[ LAUGHING ]

32:39.131 --> 32:41.089
AMEN.

32:49.837 --> 32:51.056
-[ EXHALES ]

32:58.193 --> 33:01.109
-[ SIGHS, LAUGHS ]

33:01.240 --> 33:02.981
[ SIGHS SLOWLY ]

33:03.111 --> 33:06.810
-BULLSHIT. WE ACTUALLY CATCH ONE
OF 'EM, AND WHAT HAPPENS?

33:06.941 --> 33:08.595
SHE CUTS OUR BALLS OFF.

33:08.725 --> 33:10.553
-[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU GOTTA ADMIT, THOUGH,

33:10.684 --> 33:12.991
LOOKS LIKE SHE HAD HERSELF
PLENTY OF PRACTICE.

33:13.121 --> 33:14.862
[ LAUGHS ]
[ CAN FIZZES ]

33:14.993 --> 33:17.125
-I DON'T GIVE A SHIT
WHAT SHE SAYS.

33:17.256 --> 33:19.606
I'M-A GET THAT BOY.

33:19.736 --> 33:21.303
I'M GOIN' HUNTIN'.

33:21.434 --> 33:24.698
NEXT TIME HE'S CAUGHT,
HE'S DEAD.

33:24.828 --> 33:26.917
-YOU DAMN RIGHT.
-MM-HMM.

33:27.048 --> 33:29.050
-YEAH, GOT IT.
ALL RIGHT. THANKS.

33:29.181 --> 33:30.878
-WELL?
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

33:31.009 --> 33:33.881
-STATE WON'T AUTHORIZE A DRAG
UNTIL WE DO A FULL SEARCH.

33:34.012 --> 33:36.057
BUDGET ISSUES.
-YEAH, BIG SURPRISE.

33:36.188 --> 33:38.233
-WE'LL HAVE TO ORGANIZE
A SEARCH PARTY TOMORROW.

33:38.364 --> 33:39.887
I'M THINKING MAYBE A DOZEN MEN.

33:40.018 --> 33:41.497
WE'LL GO OUT TO WHERE
WE FOUND THE TRUCK

33:41.628 --> 33:44.152
AND JUST DO A FULL SWEEP
IN EVERY DIRECTION.

33:44.283 --> 33:45.588
-THAT INCLUDE
GOING UP THE MOUNTAIN?

33:45.719 --> 33:47.199
YOU SAID NO WAY
HE'D GO UP THERE.

33:47.329 --> 33:48.939
-WE'LL SAVE THAT FOR LAST.

33:49.070 --> 33:52.117
WHAT IN THE FLYIN'...
OH, COME ON.

33:52.247 --> 33:53.727
YOU MISSIN' SOMETHIN'?

33:53.857 --> 33:54.989
-WHAT?
-ALL RIGHT, GUYS, LET'S GO.

33:55.120 --> 33:56.469
-[ LAUGHING ]
-COME ON. COME ON.

33:56.599 --> 33:58.036
GET OUT OUT OF HERE.
-NOT ME, DEPUTY DAWG.

33:58.166 --> 33:59.863
YOU KNOW WHAT I AM?
-YOU GOT TO BE KIDDING.

33:59.994 --> 34:02.127
-BUCK NAKED APPEARS TO BE
THE OBVIOUS THING.

34:02.257 --> 34:04.346
-I AM FREE.

34:04.477 --> 34:07.262
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN MY WHOLE
MISERABLE DAMN LIFE,

34:07.393 --> 34:09.134
I AM FREE.

34:09.264 --> 34:11.788
-YEAH, WELL, I'M AFRAID THAT
FEELING'S GONNA BE SHORT-LIVED.

34:11.919 --> 34:13.312
COME ALONG WITH US.

34:13.442 --> 34:16.054
-I'M WARNING YOU.
I AIN'T PUTTIN' NOTHIN' ON.

34:16.184 --> 34:18.665
-YEAH, JUST THESE.

34:18.795 --> 34:21.842
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

34:29.415 --> 34:30.764
[ CONVERSATIONS STOP ]

34:30.894 --> 34:32.418
-I'M HERE FOR ONE REASON --

34:32.548 --> 34:35.073
MY QUEEN -- SHE BELIEVES
IN OUR CUSTOMS.

34:35.203 --> 34:36.552
I RESPECT HER WISHES.

34:36.683 --> 34:38.467
NOW LET'S GET ON WITH IT
AND QUICK.

34:40.817 --> 34:44.560
-RUMORS AND STORIES
ARE ABOUNDING.

34:44.691 --> 34:46.345
WE CURIOUS TO KNOW HOW IT WAS

34:46.475 --> 34:49.348
YOU PUT HOT METAL INTO
THAT BOY'S ONE GOOD LEG.

34:53.308 --> 34:55.136
CRAIGIN O'FARRELL?

35:00.446 --> 35:02.143
-I WAS ASKED TO DELIVER

35:02.274 --> 35:05.451
A PARTICULAR SAVORY BATCH
OF WINE TO OUR BREN'IN.

35:05.581 --> 35:09.194
I WAS CARRYING MY BREW
TO HIS HOUSE, AS INSTRUCTED.

35:09.324 --> 35:12.110
OUTSIDE OF IT, I SEEN THESE BOYS
HORSIN' AROUND --

35:12.240 --> 35:16.897
ENOCH AND GRIORGAIR AND PHIL'UP.

35:17.027 --> 35:19.029
WHEN I CROSSED INTO THE ABODE,

35:19.160 --> 35:22.032
OUR BREN'IN GOT IMMEDIATELY
UPSET AT HIS SENTRY WARDS --

35:22.163 --> 35:23.947
THEM BOYS THERE.

35:24.078 --> 35:26.776
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]
HE RUSHED OUT WITH HIS GUN,

35:26.907 --> 35:28.126
SHOT THAT MAN IN THE LEG.

35:28.256 --> 35:30.519
-HE HAVE REASON TO DO SO?

35:34.262 --> 35:36.134
-THAT I CANNOT SAY.

35:40.747 --> 35:43.184
-YOUNG MAN?

35:56.110 --> 35:58.243
-IT WAS MY FAULT ENTIRELY.

35:58.373 --> 36:01.637
[ MURMURING ]

36:01.768 --> 36:04.597
-I WAS ALSO WITNESS
TO THE EVENT.

36:08.992 --> 36:12.648
YES, THEM BOYS WERE HAVING
THEMSELVES A BENJO TIME.

36:12.779 --> 36:15.738
ENOCH HERE WAS LAUGHIN'
AND CARRYIN' ON,

36:15.869 --> 36:17.653
SO HE WAS THE ONE THAT GOT SHOT.

36:23.790 --> 36:27.097
OUR FORMER BREN'IN, LADY RAY --

36:27.228 --> 36:29.839
SHE TAUGHT ME THAT GUNS
MADE A MAN WEAK,

36:29.970 --> 36:33.887
THAT THEY CAUSED MORE BLOOD
TO BE SPILLED THAN PREVENTED.

36:37.238 --> 36:40.154
OUR NEW BREN'IN IS RIGHT.

36:40.285 --> 36:44.811
HE KNOWS THAT WE HAVE A WAR
TO FIGHT NOW.

36:44.941 --> 36:47.988
HE KNOWS THAT WE NEED
TO PAY ATTENTION,

36:48.118 --> 36:49.772
'CAUSE THEM LOWLAND COWARDS --

36:49.903 --> 36:51.731
THEY COULD BE UPON US
ANY MOMENT.

36:51.861 --> 36:56.214
SO OUR DAYS OF LAUGHIN'
AND CARRYIN' ON -- THEY'RE GONE.

36:56.344 --> 37:00.174
I SAY THAT WITH SADNESS,
BUT I SAY IT STILL.

37:02.872 --> 37:05.875
OUR BREN'IN IS OUR BREN'IN,

37:06.006 --> 37:10.140
AND HIS WORD IS NOT JUST
OUR LAW...

37:10.271 --> 37:12.099
IT'S OUR TRUTH.

37:12.230 --> 37:15.407
♪♪

37:36.210 --> 37:38.299
-[ RAGGED BREATHING ]

37:43.348 --> 37:46.046
[ PANTING AND GRUNTING ]

37:46.176 --> 37:49.267
[ GRUNTING CONTINUES ]

37:49.397 --> 37:52.182
♪♪

37:52.313 --> 37:53.706
[ GROANS ]

37:53.836 --> 37:56.839
[ GRUNTING CONTINUES ]

38:08.373 --> 38:11.245
-WADE! DINNER'S READY!

38:18.165 --> 38:19.819
-ANDI-RAE.

38:21.777 --> 38:24.040
-WELL, IT'S ABOUT TIME.

38:24.171 --> 38:26.260
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

38:26.391 --> 38:28.393
-WHAT -- WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?

38:28.523 --> 38:29.872
-SIT DOWN.

38:30.003 --> 38:33.311
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU HAVEN'T
HAD A MEAL IN AGES.

38:38.185 --> 38:39.534
-[ PANTING ]

38:39.665 --> 38:40.970
I'M SO HUNGRY.

38:41.101 --> 38:43.495
-GOT YOUR FAVORITE
MAC AND CHEESE GOIN'.

38:43.625 --> 38:47.107
FOOD'S READY! YOU HEAR ME?

38:51.285 --> 38:53.156
-MAC AND CHEESE AGAIN? [ SIGHS ]

38:53.287 --> 38:56.334
DIDN'T WE JUST HAVE THIS, UH,
LAST NIGHT?

38:56.464 --> 38:59.075
[ CHUCKLES ]
-DAD?

38:59.206 --> 39:01.469
-YOU GOT YOURSELF
A PRINCESS HERE, WADE.

39:01.600 --> 39:03.036
WHAT A COOK, TOO.

39:03.166 --> 39:04.951
-WELL, FLATTERY WILL GET YOU
EVERYWHERE.

39:05.081 --> 39:06.213
-[ LAUGHS ]

39:06.344 --> 39:07.606
-NOW EAT, HONEY.

39:07.736 --> 39:09.347
-GO ON, SON. EAT.

39:15.570 --> 39:16.832
MMM.

39:25.450 --> 39:27.321
-ANDI-RAE?

39:32.152 --> 39:33.806
WHERE DID YOU GO?

39:37.113 --> 39:39.507
♪♪

39:43.337 --> 39:44.860
-BE CAREFUL.

39:44.991 --> 39:47.210
OH, CAREFUL. CAREFUL.
-OKAY, I'LL BE CAREFUL.

39:48.473 --> 39:50.388
-CAREFUL.
-I CAN MAKE IT BETTER.

39:50.518 --> 39:52.868
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
-MM-HMM.

39:52.999 --> 39:54.870
-IT'S ASA.
-MM.

39:55.001 --> 39:57.090
[ POUNDING ON DOOR ]

39:59.353 --> 40:02.487
HEY. HASIL HERE?

40:02.617 --> 40:05.446
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
JESUS CHRIST.

40:05.577 --> 40:07.056
THE HELL HAPPENED TO YOU?

40:07.187 --> 40:10.233
-UM... [ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

40:10.364 --> 40:12.366
GOT ME A JOB. [ CHUCKLES ]

40:12.497 --> 40:13.889
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN YOU GOT A JOB?

40:14.020 --> 40:15.500
-HE GOT IT AND HE QUIT ALREADY.

40:15.630 --> 40:16.762
-HEY.
-HERE.

40:16.892 --> 40:18.546
-HEY.

40:18.677 --> 40:21.027
WE, UH, WE KEPT A LITTLE BIT
FOR OURSELVES.

40:21.157 --> 40:22.681
THE REST OF THAT'S FOR YOU.

40:24.030 --> 40:25.423
-[ SCOFFS ]

40:25.553 --> 40:28.687
-IF THERE'S ANYTHING I CAN DO
TO HELP, COUSIN.

40:30.079 --> 40:32.821
-LOOK, I-I'M --
-HE NEEDS TO REST.

40:36.477 --> 40:38.523
-SHE'S THE BOSS.

40:44.398 --> 40:48.837
-LIE DOWN.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

40:48.968 --> 40:51.536
-AH! [ GROANS ]

40:51.666 --> 40:53.668
[ DOOR LOCKS ]

40:53.799 --> 40:55.365
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

40:57.411 --> 40:58.891
-I'M THE BOSS?

40:59.021 --> 41:00.849
-[ GRUNTS ]

41:00.980 --> 41:03.417
I THINK I MAY BE, UH...
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:03.548 --> 41:05.419
I MAY BE A LITTLE...

41:05.550 --> 41:07.290
[ Strained voice ]
LITTLE BIT HURT FOR THIS.

41:10.424 --> 41:12.818
-HERE... [ KISSES] AND THERE...
[ KISSES ]

41:12.948 --> 41:14.428
-JUST TAKE YOUR SHIRT OFF.

41:14.559 --> 41:16.169
-[ GIGGLES ]
ALL RIGHT, TAKIN' IT OFF.

41:16.299 --> 41:17.518
-[ LAUGHS ]

41:17.649 --> 41:20.565
[ ANIMALS HOWLING IN DISTANCE ]

41:22.697 --> 41:25.874
[ FLAMES CRACKLING ]

41:26.005 --> 41:28.921
♪♪

41:30.488 --> 41:33.708
[ FLOORBOARD CREAKS,
OWL HOOTING IN DISTANCE ]

41:37.538 --> 41:42.238
[ CLATTER ]
-[ GASPS, CHOKING ]

41:47.243 --> 41:48.418
-FOSTER!

41:48.549 --> 41:50.899
GODDAMN IT!

41:51.030 --> 41:53.380
AH! FOSTER!

41:53.511 --> 41:54.686
[ GRUNTS ]

41:54.816 --> 41:56.514
BREATHE! BREATHE.

41:56.644 --> 41:58.254
SHIT!

41:58.385 --> 42:00.474
-[ COUGHS ]
-AW, MAN, IT'S NOT WORTH IT.

42:00.605 --> 42:02.258
-[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
-IT'S NOT WORTH IT.

42:02.389 --> 42:04.739
-GET YOUR DAMN HANDS OFF ME.

42:04.870 --> 42:09.309
[ SOBBING ]

42:09.439 --> 42:12.530
-FOSTER, LISTEN TO ME.
[ PANTING ]

42:12.660 --> 42:16.229
WHATEVER IT WAS, WHOEVER IT WAS
THAT MADE YOU CLIMB UP THERE,

42:16.359 --> 42:18.884
THEY'RE THE ONES WHO'S LOST.
YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

42:19.014 --> 42:22.583
-[ PANTING ]

42:22.714 --> 42:24.367
YOU DO ME A FAVOR.

42:24.498 --> 42:28.023
JUST STAY THE HELL
OUT OF MY BUSINESS.

42:28.154 --> 42:31.940
-I'M AFRAID I CAN'T DO THAT...
COUSIN.

42:32.071 --> 42:33.899
WE'RE BLOOD.

42:39.644 --> 42:44.257
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPART ]

43:13.416 --> 43:16.419
-[ SIPS ]
[ CLATTERS ]

43:16.550 --> 43:20.641
[ ANIMAL HOWLS IN DISTANCE ]

43:20.772 --> 43:23.688
♪♪

43:27.343 --> 43:29.084
-FOLLOW ME, SIR.

43:31.434 --> 43:34.742
♪♪

43:49.931 --> 43:51.890
WE'RE DECIDED.

43:52.020 --> 43:53.456
WE'LL NOT SIT BY IDLY

43:53.587 --> 43:55.589
AND LET THE FALSE BREN'IN
CRUSH US INTO DUST,

43:55.720 --> 43:59.245
DEFILE GOOD,
UPHOLD THE MOST CRAVEN IMPULSES.

43:59.375 --> 44:02.552
OUR POWER IS OUR BOND,
NOT OUR FIRE.

44:02.683 --> 44:04.467
AND WE'RE GONNA FIGHT BACK.

44:07.514 --> 44:10.082
ARE YOU WITH US, ASA FARRELL?

44:10.212 --> 44:13.041
♪♪

44:19.352 --> 44:21.223
-GED-GEDYAH.

44:21.354 --> 44:24.574
-GED-GEDYAH.
